{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So what's image got do with it?"},{"time":3000,"text":"And I must say, I think Emeka is trying to send"},{"time":5000,"text":"a lot of subliminal messages,"},{"time":6000,"text":"because I'm going to keep harping on some of the issues"},{"time":8000,"text":"that have come up."},{"time":10000,"text":"But I'm going to try and do something different,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and try and just close the loop with some of my personal stories,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and try and put a face to a lot of the issues"},{"time":19000,"text":"that we've been talking about."},{"time":21000,"text":"So, Africa is a complex continent full of contradictions,"},{"time":24000,"text":"as you can see."},{"time":25000,"text":"We're not the only ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"And you know, it's amazing."},{"time":39000,"text":"I mean, we need a whole conference"},{"time":40000,"text":"just devoted to telling the good stories about the continent."},{"time":43000,"text":"Just think about that, you know?"},{"time":45000,"text":"And this is typically what we've been talking about,"},{"time":48000,"text":"the role that the media plays in focusing"},{"time":50000,"text":"just on the negative stuff."},{"time":52000,"text":"Now, why is that a problem?"},{"time":55000,"text":"A typical disaster story:"},{"time":58000,"text":"disease, corruption, poverty."},{"time":60000,"text":"And some of you might be standing here thinking,"},{"time":63000,"text":"saying, \"OK, you know, Ory, you're Harvard-educated,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and all you privileged people come here, saying,"},{"time":70000,"text":"'Forget the poor people."},{"time":71000,"text":"Let's focus on business and the markets, and whatever.' \""},{"time":75000,"text":"And they're all, \"There's the 80 percent of Africans"},{"time":77000,"text":"who really need help.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"And I want to tell you that this is my story, OK?"},{"time":84000,"text":"And it's the story of many of the Africans who are here."},{"time":89000,"text":"We start with poverty."},{"time":90000,"text":"I didn't grow up in the slums or anything that dire,"},{"time":93000,"text":"but I know what it is to grow up without having money,"},{"time":96000,"text":"or being able to support family."},{"time":100000,"text":"Euvin was talking about bellwether signs."},{"time":102000,"text":"The bellwether for whether our family was broke or not was breakfast."},{"time":107000,"text":"You know, when things were good, we had eggs and sausages."},{"time":110000,"text":"When things were bad, we had porridge."},{"time":113000,"text":"And like many African families,"},{"time":115000,"text":"my parents could never save"},{"time":116000,"text":"because they supported siblings, cousins, you know, their parents,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and things were always dicey."},{"time":125000,"text":"Now, when I was born, they realized they had a pretty smart kid,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and they didn't want me to go to the neighborhood school,"},{"time":131000,"text":"which was free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"And they adopted a very interesting"},{"time":135000,"text":"approach to education, which was"},{"time":137000,"text":"they were going to take me to a school that they can barely afford."},{"time":141000,"text":"So they took me to a private, Catholic, elementary school,"},{"time":144000,"text":"which set the foundation for what ended up being my career."},{"time":149000,"text":"And what happened was,"},{"time":151000,"text":"because they could afford it sometimes, sometimes not,"},{"time":154000,"text":"I got kicked out pretty much every term."},{"time":156000,"text":"You know, someone would come in with a list"},{"time":161000,"text":"of the people who haven't paid school fees,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and when they started getting pretty strict,"},{"time":165000,"text":"you had to leave, until your school fees could be paid."},{"time":167000,"text":"And I remember thinking, I mean,"},{"time":169000,"text":"why don't these guys just take me to a cheap school?"},{"time":172000,"text":"Because you know, as a kid"},{"time":174000,"text":"you're embarrassed and"},{"time":178000,"text":"you're sensitive, and everyone knows"},{"time":179000,"text":"you guys don't have money."},{"time":180000,"text":"But they kept at it,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and I now understand why they did what they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"They talk about corruption."},{"time":190000,"text":"In Kenya, we have an entrance exam to go into high school."},{"time":196000,"text":"And there's national schools, which are like the best schools,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and provincial schools."},{"time":201000,"text":"My dream school at that time was Kenya High School,"},{"time":203000,"text":"a national school."},{"time":204000,"text":"I missed the cutoff by one point."},{"time":205000,"text":"And I was so disappointed, and I was like,"},{"time":208000,"text":"\"Oh my God, you know, what am I going to do?\""},{"time":211000,"text":"And my father said, \"OK, listen."},{"time":212000,"text":"Let's go and try and talk to the headmistress."},{"time":214000,"text":"You know, it's just one point. I mean,"},{"time":216000,"text":"maybe she'll let you in if that slot's still there.\""},{"time":219000,"text":"So we went to the school,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and because we were nobodies, and because we didn't have privilege,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and because my father didn't have the right last name,"},{"time":232000,"text":"he was treated like dirt."},{"time":234000,"text":"And I sat and listened to the headmistress talk to him, saying,"},{"time":238000,"text":"you know, who do you think you are?"},{"time":239000,"text":"And, you know, you must be joking if you think"},{"time":243000,"text":"you can get a slot."},{"time":244000,"text":"And I had gone to school with other girls, who were kids of politicians,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and who had done much, much worse than I did,"},{"time":251000,"text":"and they had slots there."},{"time":254000,"text":"And there's nothing worse than seeing your parent"},{"time":256000,"text":"being humiliated in front of you, you know?"},{"time":259000,"text":"And we left, and I swore to myself,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and I was like, \"I'm never, ever going to have"},{"time":264000,"text":"to beg for anything in my life.\""},{"time":265000,"text":"They called me two weeks later, they're like,"},{"time":267000,"text":"oh, yeah, you can come now. And I told them to stuff it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"Final story, and I sort of have to speak quickly."},{"time":278000,"text":"Disease."},{"time":279000,"text":"My father, who I've been talking about, died of AIDS in 1999."},{"time":286000,"text":"He never told anyone that he had AIDS,"},{"time":288000,"text":"his fear of the stigma was so strong."},{"time":291000,"text":"And I'm pretty much the one who figured it out, because I was a nerd."},{"time":296000,"text":"And I was in the States at the time,"},{"time":298000,"text":"and they called me. He was very sick, the first time he got sick."},{"time":301000,"text":"And he had Cryptococcal meningitis."},{"time":304000,"text":"And so I went on to Google, Cryptococcal meningitis, you know."},{"time":307000,"text":"Because of doctor-patient privilege,"},{"time":310000,"text":"they couldn't really tell us what was going on."},{"time":311000,"text":"But they were like, you know, this is a long-term thing."},{"time":314000,"text":"And when I went online and looked at the infectious --"},{"time":318000,"text":"read about the disease,"},{"time":322000,"text":"I pretty much realized what was going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"The first time he got sick, he recovered."},{"time":327000,"text":"But what happened was that he had to be on medication"},{"time":329000,"text":"that, at that time -- Diflucan, which in the States"},{"time":332000,"text":"is used for yeast infections -- cost 30 dollars a pill."},{"time":336000,"text":"He had to be on that pill for the rest of his life."},{"time":342000,"text":"You know, so money ran out."},{"time":344000,"text":"He got sick again."},{"time":346000,"text":"And up until that time, he had a friend who used to travel to India,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and he used to import, bring him, could"},{"time":354000,"text":"get him a generic version of it."},{"time":356000,"text":"And that kept him going."},{"time":358000,"text":"But the money ran out."},{"time":360000,"text":"He got sick again. He got sick on a Friday."},{"time":363000,"text":"At that time, there was only one bank that had ATMs in Kenya,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and we could not get cash. The family couldn't get cash"},{"time":373000,"text":"for him to start the treatment until Monday."},{"time":376000,"text":"The hospital put him on a water drip for three days."},{"time":381000,"text":"And finally, we figured, well, OK,"},{"time":384000,"text":"we'd better just try and take him to a public hospital."},{"time":386000,"text":"At least he'll get treated"},{"time":387000,"text":"while we try to figure out the money situation."},{"time":389000,"text":"And he died when the ambulance was coming"},{"time":391000,"text":"to the hospital to take him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"And, you know, now, imagine if -- and I could go on and on --"},{"time":399000,"text":"imagine if this is all you know about me."},{"time":402000,"text":"How would you look at me?"},{"time":406000,"text":"With pity, you know. Sadness."},{"time":410000,"text":"And this is how you look at Africa."},{"time":413000,"text":"This is the damage it causes."},{"time":415000,"text":"You don't see the other side of me."},{"time":417000,"text":"You don't see the blogger,"},{"time":418000,"text":"you don't see the Harvard-educated lawyer,"},{"time":420000,"text":"the vibrant person, you know?"},{"time":423000,"text":"And I just wanted to personalize that."},{"time":425000,"text":"Because we talk about it in big terms,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and you wonder, you know, so what?"},{"time":430000,"text":"But it's damaging."},{"time":433000,"text":"And I'm not unique, right?"},{"time":435000,"text":"Imagine if all you knew about William"},{"time":437000,"text":"was the fact that he grew up in a poor village."},{"time":440000,"text":"And you didn't know about the windmill, you know?"},{"time":443000,"text":"And I was just moved."},{"time":445000,"text":"I was actually crying during his presentation."},{"time":448000,"text":"He was like, I try and I make."},{"time":450000,"text":"I was like Nike should hire him, you know, \"Just do it!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"And this is, again, the point I'm trying to make."},{"time":457000,"text":"When you focus just on the disasters --"},{"time":459000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":470000,"text":"-- we're ignoring the potential."},{"time":473000,"text":"So, what is to be done?"},{"time":477000,"text":"First of all,"},{"time":478000,"text":"Africans, we need to get better at telling our stories."},{"time":481000,"text":"We heard about that yesterday."},{"time":483000,"text":"We had some of them this morning."},{"time":485000,"text":"And this is an example, you know,"},{"time":487000,"text":"blogging is one way of doing that."},{"time":489000,"text":"Afrigator is an aggregator of African blogs"},{"time":492000,"text":"that was developed in South Africa."},{"time":495000,"text":"So we need to start getting better."},{"time":496000,"text":"If no one else will tell our stories, let's do it."},{"time":499000,"text":"And going back to the point I was trying to make,"},{"time":500000,"text":"this is the Swahili Wikipedia."},{"time":504000,"text":"Swahili is spoken by about 50 million people in East Africa."},{"time":508000,"text":"It only has five contributors."},{"time":511000,"text":"Four of them are white males -- non-native speakers."},{"time":515000,"text":"The other person is -- Ndesanjo, if you're here, stand up --"},{"time":520000,"text":"is a Tanzanian, [the] first Swahili blogger."},{"time":523000,"text":"He's the only African who's contributing to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526000,"text":"People, please. We can't whine and complain"},{"time":530000,"text":"the West is doing this."},{"time":531000,"text":"What are we doing?"},{"time":534000,"text":"Where are the rest of the Swahili speakers?"},{"time":536000,"text":"Why are we not generating our own content?"},{"time":538000,"text":"You know, it's not enough to complain. We need to act."},{"time":542000,"text":"Reuters now integrates African blogs"},{"time":545000,"text":"into their coverage of Africa."},{"time":547000,"text":"So, that's a start,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and we've heard of all their other initiatives."},{"time":551000,"text":"The cheetah generation."},{"time":552000,"text":"The aid approach, you know, is flawed."},{"time":556000,"text":"And after all the hoopla of Live 8,"},{"time":558000,"text":"we're still not anywhere in the picture."},{"time":561000,"text":"No, you're not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"But the point I'm trying to make, though,"},{"time":577000,"text":"is that it's not enough for us to criticize."},{"time":581000,"text":"And for those of you in the diaspora"},{"time":583000,"text":"who are struggling with where should I be,"},{"time":585000,"text":"should I move back,"},{"time":586000,"text":"should I stay?"},{"time":587000,"text":"You know, just jump."},{"time":589000,"text":"The continent needs you."},{"time":592000,"text":"And I can't emphasize that enough, you know."},{"time":594000,"text":"I walked away from a job with one of the top firms in D.C.,"},{"time":599000,"text":"Covington and Burling, six figures."},{"time":601000,"text":"With two paychecks, or three paychecks,"},{"time":603000,"text":"I could solve a lot of my family's problems."},{"time":606000,"text":"But I walked away from that, because my passion was here,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and because I wanted to do things that were fulfilling."},{"time":613000,"text":"And because I'm needed here, you know?"},{"time":617000,"text":"I probably can win a prize for the most ways"},{"time":620000,"text":"to use a Harvard Law School degree"},{"time":622000,"text":"because of all the things I'm doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"One is because I'm pretty aggressive,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and I try and find, you know, opportunities."},{"time":628000,"text":"But there is such a need, you know?"},{"time":631000,"text":"I'm a corporate lawyer most of the time"},{"time":632000,"text":"for an organization called Enablis"},{"time":634000,"text":"that supports entrepreneurs in South Africa."},{"time":637000,"text":"We're now moving into East Africa."},{"time":640000,"text":"And we give them business development services,"},{"time":643000,"text":"as well as financing loan and equity."},{"time":647000,"text":"I've also set up a project in Kenya,"},{"time":649000,"text":"and what we do is we track the performance"},{"time":651000,"text":"of Kenyan MPs."},{"time":652000,"text":"My partner, M, who's a tech guru, hacked WordPress."},{"time":656000,"text":"It costs us, like, 20 dollars a month just for hosting."},{"time":658000,"text":"Everything else on there is a labor of love."},{"time":662000,"text":"We've manually entered all the data there."},{"time":664000,"text":"And you can get profiles of each MP,"},{"time":667000,"text":"questions they've asked in parliament."},{"time":669000,"text":"We have a comment function,"},{"time":671000,"text":"where people can ask their MPs questions."},{"time":673000,"text":"There are some MPs who participate,"},{"time":675000,"text":"and come back and ask."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"And basically, we started this because we were tired"},{"time":678000,"text":"of complaining about our politicians."},{"time":681000,"text":"You know, I believe that accountability stems from demand."},{"time":684000,"text":"You're not just going to be accountable"},{"time":686000,"text":"out of the goodness of your heart."},{"time":687000,"text":"And we as Africans need to start challenging our leaders."},{"time":690000,"text":"What are they doing?"},{"time":692000,"text":"You know, they're not going to change"},{"time":693000,"text":"just out of nowhere."},{"time":695000,"text":"So we need new policies, we need --"},{"time":697000,"text":"where's that coming from, you know?"},{"time":699000,"text":"Another thing is that these leaders"},{"time":701000,"text":"are a reflection of our society."},{"time":704000,"text":"We talk about African governments"},{"time":706000,"text":"like they've been dropped from Mars, you know?"},{"time":709000,"text":"They come from us."},{"time":711000,"text":"And what is it about our society that is generating leaders that we don't like?"},{"time":715000,"text":"And how can we change that?"},{"time":717000,"text":"So Mzalendo was one small way we thought we could start"},{"time":721000,"text":"inspiring people to start holding their leaders accountable."},{"time":725000,"text":"Where do we go from here?"},{"time":727000,"text":"I believe in the power of ideas."},{"time":729000,"text":"I believe in the power of sharing knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"And I'd ask all of you, when you leave here, please just share,"},{"time":736000,"text":"and keep the ideas that you've gotten out of here going,"},{"time":739000,"text":"because it can make a difference."},{"time":742000,"text":"The other thing I want to urge you to do"},{"time":744000,"text":"is take an interest in the individual."},{"time":747000,"text":"I've had lots of conversations about things I think"},{"time":750000,"text":"need to be happening in Africa."},{"time":752000,"text":"People are like, \"OK, if you don't do aid,"},{"time":754000,"text":"I'm a bleeding heart liberal, what can I do?\""},{"time":757000,"text":"And when I talk about my ideas, they're like,"},{"time":758000,"text":"\"BBut it's not scalable, you know."},{"time":760000,"text":"Give me something I can do with Paypal.\""},{"time":762000,"text":"It's not that easy, you know?"},{"time":764000,"text":"And sometimes just taking an interest in the individual,"},{"time":768000,"text":"in the fellows you've met, and the businesspeople you've met,"},{"time":771000,"text":"it can make a huge difference, especially in Africa,"},{"time":773000,"text":"because usually the individual in Africa"},{"time":775000,"text":"carries a lot of people behind them."},{"time":777000,"text":"Practically. I mean, when I was a first-year student in law school,"},{"time":782000,"text":"my mom's business had collapsed, so I was supporting her."},{"time":786000,"text":"My sister was struggling to get through undergrad."},{"time":788000,"text":"I was helping her pay her tuition."},{"time":790000,"text":"My cousin ran out of school fees, and she's really smart."},{"time":793000,"text":"I was paying her school fees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"A cousin of mine died of AIDS, left an orphan,"},{"time":797000,"text":"so we said, well, what are we going to do with her?"},{"time":799000,"text":"You know, she's now my baby sister."},{"time":801000,"text":"And because of the opportunities that were afforded to me,"},{"time":803000,"text":"I am able to lift all those people."},{"time":805000,"text":"So, don't underestimate that."},{"time":809000,"text":"An example. This man changed my life."},{"time":811000,"text":"He's a professor. He's now at Vanderbilt."},{"time":813000,"text":"He's an undergrad professor, Mitchell Seligson."},{"time":816000,"text":"And because of him, I got into Harvard Law School,"},{"time":818000,"text":"because he took an interest."},{"time":819000,"text":"I was taking a class of his, and he was just like,"},{"time":823000,"text":"this is an overeager student,"},{"time":825000,"text":"which we don't normally get in the United States,"},{"time":827000,"text":"because everyone else is cynical and jaded."},{"time":831000,"text":"He called me to his office and said,"},{"time":832000,"text":"\"What do you want to do when you grow up?\""},{"time":833000,"text":"I said, \"I want to be a lawyer.\""},{"time":834000,"text":"And he was like, \"Why? You know,"},{"time":837000,"text":"we don't need another lawyer in the United States.\""},{"time":839000,"text":"And he tried to talk me out of it,"},{"time":841000,"text":"but it was like, \"OK, I know nothing about applying to law school,"},{"time":844000,"text":"I'm poli-sci Ph.D."},{"time":845000,"text":"But, you know, let's figure out what I need you to do,"},{"time":849000,"text":"what I need to do to help you out.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"It was like, \"Where do you want to go?\""},{"time":852000,"text":"And to me at that time university --"},{"time":853000,"text":"I was at University of Pitts for undergrad,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and that was like heaven, OK,"},{"time":857000,"text":"because compared to what could have been in Kenya."},{"time":859000,"text":"So I'm like, \"Yeah, I'm just applying to Pitt for law school.\""},{"time":862000,"text":"He was like, \"Why? You know, you're smart,"},{"time":864000,"text":"you have all these things going for you.\""},{"time":866000,"text":"And I'm like, \"Because I'm here and it's cheap,"},{"time":868000,"text":"and you know, I kind of like Pittsburgh.\""},{"time":871000,"text":"Like, that's the dumbest reason I've ever heard"},{"time":873000,"text":"for applying to law school."},{"time":875000,"text":"And, you know, so he took me under his wing, and he encouraged me."},{"time":879000,"text":"And he said, \"Look, you can get into Harvard,"},{"time":881000,"text":"you're that good, OK?"},{"time":882000,"text":"And if they don't admit you, they're the ones who are messed up.\""},{"time":887000,"text":"And he built me up, you know?"},{"time":889000,"text":"And this is just an illustration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"You can meet other individuals here."},{"time":893000,"text":"We just need a push."},{"time":894000,"text":"That's all I needed was a push to go to the next level."},{"time":900000,"text":"Basically, I want to end with my vision for Africa, you know?"},{"time":907000,"text":"A gentleman spoke yesterday about the indignity"},{"time":909000,"text":"of us having to leave the continent"},{"time":914000,"text":"so that we can fulfill our potential."},{"time":917000,"text":"You know, my vision is that my daughter,"},{"time":919000,"text":"and any other African child being born today,"},{"time":923000,"text":"can be whoever they want to be here,"},{"time":927000,"text":"without having to leave."},{"time":929000,"text":"And they can have the possibility of transcending"},{"time":933000,"text":"the circumstances under which they were born."},{"time":936000,"text":"That's one thing you Americans take for granted, you know?"},{"time":939000,"text":"That you can grow up, you know, not so good circumstances,"},{"time":943000,"text":"and you can move."},{"time":946000,"text":"Just because you are born in rural Arkansas, whatever,"},{"time":950000,"text":"that doesn't define who you are."},{"time":951000,"text":"For most Africans today, where you live, or where you were born,"},{"time":957000,"text":"and the circumstances under which you were born,"},{"time":960000,"text":"determine the rest of your life."},{"time":962000,"text":"I would like to see that change,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and the change starts with us."},{"time":966000,"text":"And as Africans, we need to take responsibility for our continent."},{"time":970000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}